When was the era of glory for you?

00:01:34.431 --> 00:01:36.448
Was it when you passed the exam to be a schoolteacher?

00:01:36.472 --> 00:01:38.241
Was it when you married your wife?

00:01:38.741 --> 00:01:39.771
Or...

00:01:40.371 --> 00:01:41.612
was it when your son was born?

00:01:41.812 --> 00:01:43.372
I don't have a child. I'm divorced too.

00:01:43.741 --> 00:01:44.881
What nonsense is this?

00:01:48.911 --> 00:01:49.952
My era...

00:01:53.082 --> 00:01:54.192
is now.

00:01:58.161 --> 00:02:00.097
- Get out of my class now then.
- I'm sorry.

00:02:00.121 --> 00:02:01.838
- Get out.
- I didn't know you were divorced.

00:02:01.862 --> 00:02:03.467
- I'm sorry.
- You brat. Get out now.

00:02:03.491 --> 00:02:05.107
- Get out. You little...
- Okay.

00:02:05.131 --> 00:02:07.232
Gosh. That brat. Seriously.

00:02:09.631 --> 00:02:11.901
My name is Ha Yi Chan. I'm 18 years old now.

00:02:12.071 --> 00:02:13.571
My life is twinkling to the fullest.

00:02:16.672 --> 00:02:17.842
Pedal faster!

00:02:18.511 --> 00:02:19.942
Come on. Let's go!

00:02:21.112 --> 00:02:22.881
It was the spring of 1995.

00:02:23.151 --> 00:02:24.831
There was no doubt that I was in my youth.

00:02:25.021 --> 00:02:27.721
My youth radiated without much effort that spring.

00:02:28.121 --> 00:02:31.862
I met other young kids who would change my life completely.

00:02:36.862 --> 00:02:38.762
(Used Books, The Day)

00:02:39.332 --> 00:02:40.362
Thanks.

00:02:44.672 --> 00:02:46.377
Sir, did you get any new issues of "Slam Dunk?"

00:02:46.401 --> 00:02:47.518
Check the bookshelf over there.

00:02:47.542 --> 00:02:48.542
What about "Dragon Ball?"

00:02:48.642 --> 00:02:49.962
Check the shelf above the stairs.

00:03:21.672 --> 00:03:24.912
The first person to change my life completely was...

00:03:27.811 --> 00:03:28.851
"My left hand is there..."

00:03:29.811 --> 00:03:30.882
"solely as support."

00:03:31.251 --> 00:03:34.021
Kang Baek Ho, the epitome of innocence and positive energy.

00:03:34.091 --> 00:03:36.452
He'll forever be my comic brother.

00:03:42.262 --> 00:03:43.292
Choi Se Gyeong.

00:03:43.491 --> 00:03:45.461
My queen. My muse.

00:03:46.262 --> 00:03:47.239
And...

00:03:47.263 --> 00:03:48.471
You should be in a band then.

00:03:48.771 --> 00:03:51.148
They worship guys in a band.

00:03:51.172 --> 00:03:52.941
What is this? Why did you just pop up?

00:03:53.142 --> 00:03:54.548
He's not that important. Let's skip him.

00:03:54.572 --> 00:03:56.088
Hey, wait.

00:03:56.112 --> 00:03:57.988
Why are you skipping me? What are you doing?

00:03:58.012 --> 00:03:59.382
Come here, you punk.

00:04:00.651 --> 00:04:03.582
Gosh. I'll give you a really good deal for that.

00:04:04.151 --> 00:04:06.922
I'm supposed to charge you 23 dollars.

00:04:08.691 --> 00:04:10.051
But you can buy it for 20 dollars.

00:04:10.591 --> 00:04:11.768
What's that look on your face?

00:04:11.792 --> 00:04:14.262
Okay. You have a likable face.

00:04:15.191 --> 00:04:16.232
Then...

00:04:17.191 --> 00:04:19.602
I'll be reasonable. Just give me 12 dollars.

00:04:20.461 --> 00:04:22.208
- Thank you.
- My close friend's...

00:04:22.232 --> 00:04:23.209
girlfriend's brother...

00:04:23.233 --> 00:04:25.278
goes to Baekwang High School, so I'm giving you a good deal.

00:04:25.302 --> 00:04:26.302
Okay.

00:04:27.711 --> 00:04:28.917
Kurt Cobain.

00:04:28.941 --> 00:04:31.612
The legendary band musician. The idol of the ladies.

00:04:34.652 --> 00:04:37.128
His life sparkled the most intensely, albeit briefly,

00:04:37.152 --> 00:04:39.482
and taught me a piece of truth.

00:04:39.881 --> 00:04:41.328
- Se Gyeong.
- Se Gyeong.

00:04:41.352 --> 00:04:44.097
- It's Se Gyeong.
- What's going on?

00:04:44.121 --> 00:04:46.402
- She looks great in that shirt.
- Gosh, she's so pretty.

00:04:46.922 --> 00:04:48.292
My gosh. Why is he not here?

00:04:57.772 --> 00:05:00.347
The only way to win over a beauty like her...

00:05:00.371 --> 00:05:02.018
for a poor guy with no connections like me is...

00:05:02.042 --> 00:05:03.542
I guess you like bands as well.

00:05:04.641 --> 00:05:06.081
You should've told me.

00:05:06.842 --> 00:05:07.912
Actually,

00:05:10.381 --> 00:05:11.422
I'm in a band too.

00:05:14.891 --> 00:05:15.891
Se Gyeong.

00:05:16.522 --> 00:05:18.761
Do you want to come to our concert later?

00:05:22.061 --> 00:05:23.861
My school is having a festival a month later.

00:05:24.061 --> 00:05:25.902
I will prepare a performance, just for you.

00:05:26.032 --> 00:05:27.009
Please come to watch me.

00:05:27.033 --> 00:05:28.208
Does your band actually exist?

00:05:28.232 --> 00:05:29.902
- I'm going to make one now.
- What?

00:05:30.431 --> 00:05:31.542
I bought this T-shirt.

00:05:32.042 --> 00:05:33.641
I also bought a guitar pick.

00:05:33.941 --> 00:05:35.912
I'm ready to show you my affection.

00:05:36.272 --> 00:05:38.581
I just need to start my band. You'll come, right?

00:05:39.212 --> 00:05:40.412
Why would I?

00:05:40.482 --> 00:05:41.982
I'm making the band just for you...

00:05:42.081 --> 00:05:43.557
and putting on the concert just for you too.

00:05:43.581 --> 00:05:45.552
Besides, there will be a spot, just for you.

00:05:45.722 --> 00:05:50.121
- Give him an answer.
- Give him an answer.

00:05:53.321 --> 00:05:54.568
- What?
- What's going on?

00:05:54.592 --> 00:05:56.467
Se Gyeong, I didn't peg you to be such a bold woman.

00:05:56.491 --> 00:05:58.302
- Sure.
- Really?

00:05:59.532 --> 00:06:01.831
Did you really just say, "sure?"

00:06:03.931 --> 00:06:04.941
But...

00:06:05.802 --> 00:06:07.441
- I have conditions.
- Go ahead.

00:06:07.811 --> 00:06:09.518
What are the conditions? Just tell me!

00:06:09.542 --> 00:06:10.942
But you must promise me this first.

00:06:11.282 --> 00:06:12.758
If you can't keep your promise,

00:06:12.782 --> 00:06:14.811
you will never show up in front of me ever again.

00:06:14.881 --> 00:06:17.482
Fine. But you need to promise me something too.

00:06:17.821 --> 00:06:19.722
If I keep my promise,

00:06:19.881 --> 00:06:21.722
give me a chance to be your boyfriend.

00:06:22.792 --> 00:06:24.467
The chance of that happening is close to zero.

00:06:24.491 --> 00:06:26.162
The world of possibility is unbelievable.

00:06:27.292 --> 00:06:28.991
Tell me what the conditions are.

00:06:29.261 --> 00:06:31.462
Firstly, it must be a new band.

00:06:31.532 --> 00:06:32.578
You'd better stop now...

00:06:32.602 --> 00:06:34.347
if you're thinking about joining an already successful band.

00:06:34.371 --> 00:06:36.607
Secondly, you must already know how to play an instrument.

00:06:36.631 --> 00:06:37.878
You will have to do a solo performance.

00:06:37.902 --> 00:06:39.772
Thirdly, I will pick the song.

00:06:40.001 --> 00:06:41.588
If you're thinking about picking an easy song,

00:06:41.612 --> 00:06:42.692
you might as well stop now.

00:06:43.842 --> 00:06:46.212
What do you say? Are you still in?

00:06:47.112 --> 00:06:48.987
Of course. What's the title?

00:06:49.011 --> 00:06:50.571
- What's the title?
- What's the title?

00:06:51.052 --> 00:06:52.029
What's the title?

00:06:52.053 --> 00:06:53.613
- What's the title?
- What's the title?

00:06:55.092 --> 00:06:57.321
"Come as You Are" by Nirvana.

00:07:01.761 --> 00:07:03.532
Hey, can you actually do it?

00:07:03.831 --> 00:07:06.302
- That was insane.
- Can you really do it?

00:07:17.112 --> 00:07:19.311
- Are you sure about this?
- What do you mean?

00:07:19.641 --> 00:07:20.782
The bet.

00:07:22.311 --> 00:07:23.751
What if he pulls it off?

00:07:24.652 --> 00:07:25.898
He will never be able to pull it off.

00:07:25.922 --> 00:07:27.522
How can you be so certain?

00:07:27.751 --> 00:07:28.998
I could tell just by looking at his fingers.

00:07:29.022 --> 00:07:31.398
Those weren't the hands of a man who could play an instrument.

00:07:31.422 --> 00:07:33.162
Then why did you play along?

00:07:33.462 --> 00:07:35.302
That innocent boy must be excited for nothing.

00:07:35.792 --> 00:07:37.578
He will need people to play in a band.

00:07:37.602 --> 00:07:39.562
The song by Nirvana isn't easy to perform either.

00:07:39.602 --> 00:07:41.248
He will be busy forming a band and practicing the song.

00:07:41.272 --> 00:07:42.912
He won't be bothering me for a while now.

00:07:43.402 --> 00:07:44.379
When he fails his mission,

00:07:44.403 --> 00:07:46.083
he'll be too embarrassed to show his face.

00:07:46.272 --> 00:07:48.371
But you might have overlooked something.

00:07:49.342 --> 00:07:50.319
What do you mean?

00:07:50.343 --> 00:07:52.011
A boy in love...

00:07:52.842 --> 00:07:55.881
can sometimes have superpowers.

00:07:58.282 --> 00:08:00.821
I will bet ten dollars that he will succeed.

00:08:01.422 --> 00:08:04.522
Come on. Whose side are you on?

00:08:07.162 --> 00:08:09.131
- You want to make what?
- A band.

00:08:09.662 --> 00:08:13.001
You're not talking about the Band-Aid, right?

00:08:13.232 --> 00:08:15.152
- That was a joke, right?
- You're crazy, right?

00:08:15.272 --> 00:08:17.472
Bands aren't something you can just form overnight.

00:08:17.532 --> 00:08:19.201
Apparently, that's possible.

00:08:19.741 --> 00:08:21.441
- How?
- Baekwang Band.

00:08:21.672 --> 00:08:23.212
Are you talking about our school band?

00:08:37.621 --> 00:08:39.261
Performances by attention-seekers.

00:08:39.891 --> 00:08:41.261
A group of nutcases.

00:08:41.962 --> 00:08:43.138
Every time they performed,

00:08:43.162 --> 00:08:44.338
they competed against each other to stand out.

00:08:44.362 --> 00:08:45.977
So the only sane member, their guitarist,

00:08:46.001 --> 00:08:46.978
transferred to another school.

00:08:47.002 --> 00:08:48.722
In the end, the band was forced to disband.

00:08:49.101 --> 00:08:51.278
- That Baekwang Band?
- Yes.

00:08:51.302 --> 00:08:53.547
They said yes when I promised them dates with college girls.

00:08:53.571 --> 00:08:55.891
Are you crazy? What could you possibly do with those guys?

00:08:56.512 --> 00:08:57.882
Hey, my friend.

00:08:58.581 --> 00:09:00.657
The name, Baekwang Band,

00:09:00.681 --> 00:09:04.628
has already vanished into thin air as a part of their humiliating past.

00:09:04.652 --> 00:09:05.629
So now...

00:09:05.653 --> 00:09:09.691
(First Love Memory Manipulators)

00:09:10.522 --> 00:09:11.522
Did you see that?

00:09:11.961 --> 00:09:14.492
I will be the first love of every girl out there.

00:09:14.961 --> 00:09:18.431
Se Gyeong will especially lose her memory completely.

00:09:19.032 --> 00:09:20.032
Right.

00:09:21.331 --> 00:09:22.971
You're my band's manager.

00:09:23.372 --> 00:09:24.941
- Congratulations.
- What?

00:09:25.471 --> 00:09:28.512
- Gosh. No. Never. I don't want...
- My friend.

00:09:28.772 --> 00:09:30.841
Welcome to The Manipulators.

00:09:35.512 --> 00:09:38.022
You definitely promised us dates with dance majors.

00:09:38.481 --> 00:09:40.498
I'll kill you if you bring martial arts majors.

00:09:40.522 --> 00:09:42.552
What? Have you been lied to your whole life?

00:09:42.922 --> 00:09:44.052
I'm sure you've heard of it.

00:09:44.252 --> 00:09:45.968
Getting a room in Snail Guesthouse...

00:09:45.992 --> 00:09:47.792
is harder than getting accepted into college.

00:09:48.361 --> 00:09:49.892
My grandmother runs the guesthouse.

00:09:50.861 --> 00:09:52.181
Isn't that a men-only guesthouse?

00:09:52.302 --> 00:09:54.238
No college girls can stay in that guesthouse.

00:09:54.262 --> 00:09:55.348
You must not know that...

00:09:55.372 --> 00:09:57.372
all these men go to prestigious universities.

00:09:57.902 --> 00:09:59.878
Their girlfriends are flight attendants,

00:09:59.902 --> 00:10:02.172
ballerinas, and designers.

00:10:06.012 --> 00:10:07.488
How much time do we have left until the show?

00:10:07.512 --> 00:10:09.392
We have 1 month and 10 days until the festival.

00:10:09.481 --> 00:10:11.152
- We have enough time.
- Okay.

00:10:12.282 --> 00:10:13.382
Then...

00:10:14.221 --> 00:10:16.152
show us what you got, frontman.

00:10:16.591 --> 00:10:17.622
Of course.

00:10:19.221 --> 00:10:20.691
This is the moment of truth.

00:10:35.012 --> 00:10:36.642
Two, three, four.

00:11:02.372 --> 00:11:03.532
What? Why did you stop?

00:11:05.272 --> 00:11:07.672
- Are you nervous?
- This is all I've got.

00:11:08.311 --> 00:11:10.547
How could he be so nonchalant about this?

00:11:10.571 --> 00:11:11.681
Am I the only one,

00:11:11.782 --> 00:11:13.457
itching to throw a few punches? It's been a while.

00:11:13.481 --> 00:11:15.087
Hey, I'm a vocalist.

00:11:15.111 --> 00:11:16.927
I can just do a good job with the intro.

00:11:16.951 --> 00:11:19.758
I will play by myself during the intro.

00:11:19.782 --> 00:11:22.067
You guys can play your instruments while I sing.

00:11:22.091 --> 00:11:23.152
Darn it.

00:11:23.622 --> 00:11:25.382
Do you think we're some backup band for you?

00:11:25.492 --> 00:11:29.108
If you want to sing, go to karaoke and sing by yourself.

00:11:29.132 --> 00:11:30.731
Hey, calm down.

00:11:31.302 --> 00:11:32.778
Yi Chan, just give it up.

00:11:32.802 --> 00:11:34.772
You can't have a band without a guitarist.

00:11:35.902 --> 00:11:37.231
You heard your friend, right?

00:11:37.431 --> 00:11:38.542
Unbelievable.

00:11:38.872 --> 00:11:40.502
It was awful meeting you.

00:11:40.841 --> 00:11:42.587
Let's not see each other again.

00:11:42.611 --> 00:11:43.611
Let's go.

00:11:45.081 --> 00:11:48.152
Wait!

00:11:49.211 --> 00:11:50.211
Wait.

00:11:51.181 --> 00:11:54.022
Okay. I understand what you're saying.

00:11:54.351 --> 00:11:56.552
Let's get someone then. Let's do it!

00:11:57.591 --> 00:12:00.067
I'll recruit an awesome guitarist.

00:12:00.091 --> 00:12:01.132
Are you that dumb?

00:12:01.731 --> 00:12:03.638
We don't have time to recruit a guitarist and practice with him.

00:12:03.662 --> 00:12:05.537
We'll need someone like Yoon Dong Jin to make this work.

00:12:05.561 --> 00:12:07.731
Yoon Dong Jin? Who is that?

00:12:08.971 --> 00:12:10.372
I'll bring him then!

00:12:11.032 --> 00:12:13.118
Do you even know who Yoon Dong Jin is?

00:12:13.142 --> 00:12:14.172
Dong Jin.

00:12:15.571 --> 00:12:16.711
I know him very well.

00:12:18.111 --> 00:12:19.211
I knew it.

00:12:19.782 --> 00:12:21.351
See? What did I tell you?

00:12:21.851 --> 00:12:24.628
I told you he might know Dong Jin because he's from Chuncheon.

00:12:24.652 --> 00:12:27.228
Anyone can know him. Knowing him personally matters.

00:12:27.252 --> 00:12:29.022
I know who Yoon Dong Jin is too.

00:12:29.292 --> 00:12:30.451
Yoon Dong Jin.

00:12:30.992 --> 00:12:32.337
The genius guitarist...

00:12:32.361 --> 00:12:34.608
in the second year at Chuncheon National University of Education.

00:12:34.632 --> 00:12:37.667
He gave a song he wrote at the age of 13 to a professional singer.

00:12:37.691 --> 00:12:41.101
He's a talented musician in songwriting as well.

00:12:41.372 --> 00:12:44.672
Gosh, he was one of my students, but he was indeed special.

00:12:44.772 --> 00:12:46.778
You taught Yoon Dong Jin?

00:12:46.802 --> 00:12:47.841
Oh, no.

00:12:48.512 --> 00:12:50.512
I said something I shouldn't have said.

00:12:51.681 --> 00:12:54.557
The truth is, I'm the one who taught him how to play the guitar.

00:12:54.581 --> 00:12:56.827
Gosh. Have some of this.

00:12:56.851 --> 00:12:59.122
It's nicely grilled. It's Chuncheon-style spicy chicken.

00:12:59.321 --> 00:13:00.351
Let me try it.

00:13:03.851 --> 00:13:05.162
It smells just like Chuncheon.

00:13:05.591 --> 00:13:06.662
Bal San.

00:13:07.522 --> 00:13:09.638
Can you give Dong Jin a call?

00:13:09.662 --> 00:13:12.002
- Please?
- Yi Chan, it's burning. Flip it.

00:13:13.902 --> 00:13:16.471
Hey, you're burning it. Come on.

00:13:18.672 --> 00:13:21.002
But why do you need me to call him?

00:13:21.272 --> 00:13:24.218
The truth is, he formed a band.

00:13:24.242 --> 00:13:26.858
He needs to invite a guitarist at the last minute.

00:13:26.882 --> 00:13:27.927
He must do it before the festival.

00:13:27.951 --> 00:13:30.427
Gosh. I wonder if Dong Jin will do it.

00:13:30.451 --> 00:13:31.797
Perform with a high school band?

00:13:31.821 --> 00:13:34.181
That's why I'm asking you to call him.

00:13:34.752 --> 00:13:36.067
If you don't want to talk to him directly,

00:13:36.091 --> 00:13:37.068
give me his number.

00:13:37.092 --> 00:13:38.692
I'm good at kneeling in front of people.

00:13:39.122 --> 00:13:40.191
You brat.

00:13:41.231 --> 00:13:42.231
Wait.

00:13:48.701 --> 00:13:51.218
Dong Jin is a night owl.

00:13:51.242 --> 00:13:53.242
So I don't think he will pick up the phone now.

00:13:53.701 --> 00:13:56.272
I'll call his oldest brother instead.

00:13:57.471 --> 00:13:58.481
Hey.

00:14:07.951 --> 00:14:08.968
Hello.

00:14:08.992 --> 00:14:10.522
- Hello.
- He answered it.

00:14:10.951 --> 00:14:13.292
I'm Bal San from Chuncheon.

00:14:13.561 --> 00:14:14.691
Who is this?

00:14:14.892 --> 00:14:16.691
I think you got the wrong number.

00:14:17.292 --> 00:14:18.961
