00:29:53.331 --> 00:29:55.831
Oh, I guess you saw us that day.

00:29:57.331 --> 00:29:58.601
Do I like him?

00:30:01.542 --> 00:30:03.611
No. Not at all.

00:30:09.611 --> 00:30:10.811
But I find him amusing,

00:30:11.252 --> 00:30:12.722
like a fun comic book.

00:30:13.022 --> 00:30:15.022
One that makes you curious about the next episode.

00:30:20.121 --> 00:30:21.391
Hey, Yoon Chung Ah!

00:30:22.492 --> 00:30:23.962
Oh, that's right. She can't hear.

00:30:25.432 --> 00:30:26.702
What a hassle.

00:30:32.171 --> 00:30:35.202
(The homeroom teacher said to come to the teachers' office now.)

00:30:35.542 --> 00:30:38.111
Min A, is this really your painting?

00:30:39.381 --> 00:30:40.411
Yes.

00:30:42.381 --> 00:30:44.151
The art teacher brought this...

00:30:44.252 --> 00:30:46.121
and said you kept copying Chung Ah's work.

00:30:47.222 --> 00:30:48.552
You tell us the truth.

00:30:49.421 --> 00:30:51.851
Whose painting is the original? Who copied whom?

00:30:53.091 --> 00:30:54.837
Sir, this is so unfair.

00:30:54.861 --> 00:30:55.891
What's unfair?

00:30:56.131 --> 00:30:58.768
Why are you interrogating me and not her?

00:30:58.792 --> 00:31:01.607
You're already assuming that I copied her!

00:31:01.631 --> 00:31:03.732
My goodness. Stop crying at once.

00:31:04.101 --> 00:31:05.671
You did nothing to be proud of.

00:31:06.171 --> 00:31:07.678
Thank goodness we checked before you submitted this.

00:31:07.702 --> 00:31:09.702
This would've been so embarrassing for the school.

00:31:10.071 --> 00:31:12.758
Anyway, we can't submit this to the contest. Just know that.

00:31:12.782 --> 00:31:15.542
No. Please submit it for me, sir.

00:31:15.712 --> 00:31:18.287
I need to win more awards to go to college.

00:31:18.311 --> 00:31:21.222
No. Controversial applications will be denied.

00:31:21.522 --> 00:31:22.728
That's the rule.

00:31:22.752 --> 00:31:24.632
Why are you standing there? Take your painting.

00:31:47.641 --> 00:31:49.528
See? What did I tell you?

00:31:49.552 --> 00:31:51.528
I said you wouldn't be able to fool our homeroom teacher.

00:31:51.552 --> 00:31:53.022
Shut your mouth, will you?

00:32:00.161 --> 00:32:01.192
That witch.

00:32:01.861 --> 00:32:03.408
She won't even participate in the contest anyway.

00:32:03.432 --> 00:32:05.091
Why must she get in my way?

00:32:06.161 --> 00:32:08.831
I bet she was the one who told the chairwoman on me.

00:32:09.502 --> 00:32:11.702
Chung Ah won't be participating in the contest?

00:32:12.032 --> 00:32:13.042
Why not?

00:32:13.302 --> 00:32:15.448
She's not satisfied with her painting.

00:32:15.472 --> 00:32:16.488
My gosh.

00:32:16.512 --> 00:32:18.272
She thinks she's a real artist or something.

00:32:18.641 --> 00:32:21.817
But then again, her stepmother is the chairwoman of the school.

00:32:21.841 --> 00:32:23.327
No wonder none of the teachers scares her,

00:32:23.351 --> 00:32:25.511
and she's not even worried about getting into college.

00:32:26.381 --> 00:32:28.458
She got into this school thanks to the special admission program.

00:32:28.482 --> 00:32:30.192
The one for students with disabilities.

00:32:31.252 --> 00:32:33.121
Gosh, that scared me. What's with her?

00:32:38.032 --> 00:32:40.432
- My gosh. Has she lost her mind?
- She must be going crazy.

00:32:40.802 --> 00:32:42.972
Yes, keep acting up like that.

00:32:48.341 --> 00:32:49.341
What?

00:33:02.351 --> 00:33:03.421
Hey!

00:33:04.192 --> 00:33:05.252
Oh, no!

00:33:05.651 --> 00:33:07.037
- Hey!
- Break it up!

00:33:07.061 --> 00:33:08.768
- Hey!
- What are you two doing?

00:33:08.792 --> 00:33:11.438
- Hey, stop!
- Let go!

00:33:11.462 --> 00:33:13.508
- Hey!
- Let go!

00:33:13.532 --> 00:33:15.478
- Girls!
- You two can talk it out!

00:33:15.502 --> 00:33:17.171
What? Mom was his first love?

00:33:17.671 --> 00:33:19.391
He's never loved another woman in his life?

00:33:20.841 --> 00:33:23.111
But he joined the band because of another girl?

00:33:23.671 --> 00:33:25.811
I'm so disappointed. He totally let me down.

00:33:26.282 --> 00:33:27.458
If this is a dream, I'll wake up.

00:33:27.482 --> 00:33:29.602
If this is real, I'll go back to the present at once.

00:33:32.452 --> 00:33:33.821
Wait. How do I go back?

00:33:34.581 --> 00:33:36.668
(Used Books, The Day)

00:33:36.692 --> 00:33:37.792
This is so weird.

00:33:46.331 --> 00:33:47.932
I swear, it was right here.

00:33:53.101 --> 00:33:54.671
(The Day)

00:33:56.641 --> 00:33:58.018
(Everyone needs a little sanctuary.)

00:33:58.042 --> 00:33:59.802
(We hope this place becomes your sanctuary.)

00:34:07.022 --> 00:34:09.192
Oh, hello. Can I help you find something?

00:34:09.792 --> 00:34:12.591
How long have you been running this secondhand bookstore here?

00:34:12.821 --> 00:34:14.661
About ten years.

00:34:14.792 --> 00:34:15.908
Why do you ask?

00:34:15.932 --> 00:34:18.008
Then don't you know La Vida Music? They sell musical instruments.

00:34:18.032 --> 00:34:19.161
"La Vida?"

00:34:19.831 --> 00:34:21.861
I've never heard of such a store before.

00:34:22.002 --> 00:34:23.972
It must be somewhere around here.

00:34:24.401 --> 00:34:26.201
Please try to remember if you've heard of it.

00:34:26.571 --> 00:34:28.348
I've been living and working in this area for years,

00:34:28.372 --> 00:34:30.572
but I've never heard of such a musical instrument shop.

00:34:31.412 --> 00:34:32.441
Really?

00:34:35.082 --> 00:34:36.528
I'm sorry for wasting your time.

00:34:36.552 --> 00:34:37.981
Gosh, don't worry about it.

00:34:39.151 --> 00:34:40.821
All right, then. Have a good day.

00:34:49.392 --> 00:34:50.492
No way.

00:34:51.131 --> 00:34:53.451
What if that door allows you to travel through dimensions?

00:34:55.001 --> 00:34:58.702
What if that door is the passage between the past and the present?

00:35:00.671 --> 00:35:02.372
Then, the moment I walk out the door,

00:35:03.242 --> 00:35:05.517
I could return to 2023.

00:35:05.541 --> 00:35:08.541
(The Day, Buy and Sell)

00:35:41.282 --> 00:35:43.052
(Used Books, The Day)

00:35:44.082 --> 00:35:45.158
Why am I still here?

00:35:45.182 --> 00:35:47.582
Why am I still in 1995?

00:35:48.421 --> 00:35:50.591
Was I wrong? Does the door only open at night?

00:35:52.352 --> 00:35:53.461
No way.

00:35:54.562 --> 00:35:56.362
What if I'm stuck here and can never go home?

00:35:58.091 --> 00:36:00.961
No. There must be a way.

00:36:01.302 --> 00:36:02.977
I must find a way. I will find a way.

00:36:03.001 --> 00:36:05.102
Do not lose this transaction slip.

00:36:05.802 --> 00:36:07.501
You'll be in a tight spot if you do. Okay?

00:36:27.892 --> 00:36:29.191
Oh, there's six cents left.

00:36:30.861 --> 00:36:32.808
- I'm sorry. My Wi-Fi isn't working.
- What?

00:36:32.832 --> 00:36:34.202
Sorry. I apologize.

00:36:41.602 --> 00:36:44.041
The number does not exist.

00:36:44.412 --> 00:36:46.912
Please check the number and try again.

00:36:48.082 --> 00:36:50.552
- The number does not exist.
- No!

00:36:50.981 --> 00:36:52.082
Please check the number...

00:37:01.622 --> 00:37:02.731
I'm starving.

00:37:07.802 --> 00:37:09.032
I'll give you the rest later.

00:37:18.041 --> 00:37:19.312
Come again soon!

00:37:22.111 --> 00:37:24.082
I'll have three servings of tteokbokki...

00:37:24.182 --> 00:37:25.627
and the fritters too. One of each.

00:37:25.651 --> 00:37:26.881
Sure. One moment, please.

00:37:27.452 --> 00:37:28.812
You accept 50-dollar bills, right?

00:37:28.881 --> 00:37:30.241
Gift certificates aren't accepted.

00:37:30.352 --> 00:37:32.052
I mean cash bills, not gift certificates.

00:37:36.432 --> 00:37:37.437
They're big.

00:37:37.461 --> 00:37:38.937
(10-dollar bills, 5-dollar bills)

00:37:38.961 --> 00:37:40.001
They're big.

00:37:40.702 --> 00:37:43.532
They're larger than the paper bills used in 2023.

00:37:43.771 --> 00:37:44.932
I'm sorry,

00:37:45.671 --> 00:37:48.302
but has the 50-dollar bill not been released yet?

00:37:48.771 --> 00:37:50.412
What nonsense.

00:37:51.142 --> 00:37:52.822
Anyway, do you want the tteokbokki or not?

00:38:02.651 --> 00:38:03.952
Master, darn you.

00:38:04.651 --> 00:38:06.361
If I see you again, you're so dead!

00:38:07.492 --> 00:38:09.191
If I see you again, you're so dead.

00:38:10.392 --> 00:38:13.272
I can't believe I met that imposter. I guess I should blame my bad luck.

00:38:25.742 --> 00:38:27.142
I'm home, Grandma.

00:38:27.381 --> 00:38:29.582
- Hey, you're back.
- Yes.

00:38:39.321 --> 00:38:41.062
Hey, why did you come home alone?

00:38:41.392 --> 00:38:42.392
What about your guest?

00:38:43.262 --> 00:38:44.461
- "Guest?"
- Yes.

00:38:44.662 --> 00:38:45.762
What guest?

00:38:45.832 --> 00:38:48.152
You know, from Chuncheon National University of Education.

00:38:48.602 --> 00:38:51.032
Anyway, you said you offered him room and board...

00:38:51.171 --> 00:38:53.041
in exchange for free tutoring sessions.

00:38:53.202 --> 00:38:55.147
Oh, that. I decided not to do it.

00:38:55.171 --> 00:38:56.812
- Why not?
- Grandma.

00:38:57.012 --> 00:38:58.642
I met him, and he's a con man.

00:38:58.711 --> 00:39:00.941
Why do you say that? Did he look scary?

00:39:01.041 --> 00:39:03.412
Yes, he looked so...

00:39:07.952 --> 00:39:10.598
I mean, he's got a nice face. He's quite good-looking.

00:39:10.622 --> 00:39:11.782
What? So why won't you do it?

00:39:12.892 --> 00:39:14.738
Did he look dumb?

00:39:14.762 --> 00:39:17.131
Yes! He's so...

00:39:18.131 --> 00:39:19.508
You were much more handsome than I thought,

00:39:19.532 --> 00:39:20.602
which was surprising.

00:39:23.032 --> 00:39:24.032
He looks smart.

00:39:25.032 --> 00:39:27.047
I don't know who his parents are, but he looked really smart.

00:39:27.071 --> 00:39:29.841
What? Then why didn't you bring him here?

00:39:30.211 --> 00:39:32.788
You just don't want to study. That's it, right?

00:39:32.812 --> 00:39:34.288
No, that's not it!

00:39:34.312 --> 00:39:37.552
Grandma, you don't know anything. Seriously!

00:39:38.151 --> 00:39:39.151
What in the world?

00:39:39.251 --> 00:39:42.992
Goodness. I thought it was the best thing you'd ever done.

00:39:45.021 --> 00:39:46.021
Hey.

00:39:48.492 --> 00:39:50.032
So? You two parted ways right away?

00:39:50.832 --> 00:39:53.113
Then what was I supposed to do? Have a gunfight with him?

00:39:53.162 --> 00:39:56.372
Then you should've called me and let me know.

00:39:56.832 --> 00:39:58.278
You said you'd bring him here,

00:39:58.302 --> 00:40:01.178
so I went grocery shopping and cooked up a storm all day.

00:40:01.202 --> 00:40:03.242
Why would you bother making food for him?

00:40:04.372 --> 00:40:06.317
Can't you see that your grandmother is talking?

00:40:06.341 --> 00:40:07.912
Don't you dare talk back to me.

00:40:08.512 --> 00:40:11.552
You said he came here all the way from Chuncheon.

00:40:12.082 --> 00:40:15.622
We should give him a warm welcome and take care of him.

00:40:16.021 --> 00:40:17.751
Is that how I raised you?

00:40:18.852 --> 00:40:20.861
No. I'm sorry.

00:40:23.032 --> 00:40:24.662
Wash up at once, and have some food.

00:40:25.231 --> 00:40:27.278
He must be exhausted after the long train ride.

00:40:27.302 --> 00:40:29.361
He should've at least stopped by for some food.

00:40:29.432 --> 00:40:31.602
You're so rude!

00:40:34.341 --> 00:40:35.341
Gosh.

00:40:36.941 --> 00:40:38.872
He's not a kid, so he won't starve.

00:40:40.012 --> 00:40:42.142
- Sorry, excuse me.
- Yes?

00:40:42.211 --> 00:40:45.412
I lost my wallet, so I don't have a single penny on me now.

00:40:47.182 --> 00:40:48.521
I wonder if he's eaten.

00:40:49.521 --> 00:40:50.892
He did look quite tired.

00:40:52.492 --> 00:40:53.521
What?

00:40:54.492 --> 00:40:56.832
Why do I care whether or not that jerk is starving?

00:40:57.892 --> 00:40:59.492
He's a despicable con man...

00:41:00.162 --> 00:41:02.322
and a complete stranger who has nothing to do with me!

00:41:06.242 --> 00:41:08.642
Okay, 1992...

00:41:09.302 --> 00:41:10.812
This is from 1990. Nice.

00:41:14.782 --> 00:41:15.812
This is from 1999.

00:41:19.852 --> 00:41:20.952
Oh, this is from 1991.

00:41:21.352 --> 00:41:22.452
Nice.

00:41:26.191 --> 00:41:27.461
Gosh, I feel much better now.

00:41:40.041 --> 00:41:41.071
Mom.

00:41:43.271 --> 00:41:44.972
Dad kicked me out.

00:41:48.312 --> 00:41:49.312
Mom.

00:41:52.111 --> 00:41:53.421
I feel so lost.

00:41:56.291 --> 00:41:57.321
Mom.

00:42:00.361 --> 00:42:03.432
I wish I could have your doenjang stew right now.

00:42:06.461 --> 00:42:07.562
Mom.

00:42:09.602 --> 00:42:10.702
Mom...

00:42:12.332 --> 00:42:15.541
That's right. I should look for Mom. Why hadn't I thought of that?

00:42:16.812 --> 00:42:18.771
Mom and Dad are the same age,

00:42:19.211 --> 00:42:20.812
so if I find her school...

00:42:22.142 --> 00:42:24.751
Mom, how come you don't have a single yearbook?

00:42:26.182 --> 00:42:28.952
I lost them all in a flood years ago.

00:42:31.552 --> 00:42:33.361
What about pictures of your parents?

00:42:33.861 --> 00:42:35.341
Do you have any other family members?

00:42:38.131 --> 00:42:39.231
No, I don't.

00:42:39.461 --> 00:42:41.562
I practically grew up an orphan.

00:42:42.001 --> 00:42:43.231
The rest is a secret.

00:42:44.032 --> 00:42:46.202
I'll tell you more when you're older, okay?

00:42:47.472 --> 00:42:48.472
Okay.

00:42:51.611 --> 00:42:52.611
I know nothing...

00:42:54.012 --> 00:42:55.012
about Mom.

00:43:07.722 --> 00:43:10.631
(Please use it as if it is your bathroom.)

00:43:29.642 --> 00:43:32.312
I thought I knew a lot about my parents, but I was wrong.

00:43:33.921 --> 00:43:35.521
I thought I knew enough about them,

00:43:36.691 --> 00:43:38.452
so I never made an effort to learn more.

00:43:40.921 --> 00:43:43.392
And at some point, I stopped being curious.

00:43:52.972 --> 00:43:55.041
I told you. I didn't eat it.

00:43:56.202 --> 00:43:57.571
Come on. I don't believe you.

00:44:08.481 --> 00:44:10.722
Cover yourself with it, or you'll freeze to death.

00:44:17.262 --> 00:44:19.332
My own worries always came first.

00:44:20.501 --> 00:44:22.762
My problems always took precedence over all else.

00:44:32.512 --> 00:44:33.881
I'm freezing.

00:44:36.412 --> 00:44:38.111
So I didn't know these things.

00:44:50.361 --> 00:44:52.992
The fact that Dad wasn't born deaf...

00:44:54.162 --> 00:44:56.482
and the reason Mom said she practically grew up an orphan.

00:45:07.082 --> 00:45:10.481
And that there was a time when Mom and Dad...

00:45:11.082 --> 00:45:13.481
were called by their own names, not just "Mom" and "Dad."

00:46:10.242 --> 00:46:12.448
- Hello?
- Hi, there.

00:46:12.472 --> 00:46:14.288
So? Are you enjoying your trip?

00:46:14.312 --> 00:46:15.881
Who are you, really?

00:46:16.441 --> 00:46:18.312
Why on earth are you doing this to me?

00:46:18.412 --> 00:46:19.727
Oh, no.

00:46:19.751 --> 00:46:22.127
I guess you're not really enjoying your trip.

00:46:22.151 --> 00:46:24.921
Why did you send me here?

00:46:25.151 --> 00:46:26.227
Well...

00:46:26.251 --> 00:46:28.567
Don't you think you should find the reason yourself?

00:46:28.591 --> 00:46:30.432
- Hey, mister!
- What?

00:46:33.361 --> 00:46:35.238
Then how can I go back?

00:46:35.262 --> 00:46:36.808
What can I do to return to the present?

00:46:36.832 --> 00:46:37.872
Well...

00:46:38.071 --> 00:46:40.271
That too. You'll have to figure it out on your own.

00:46:41.341 --> 00:46:43.488
Then give me a hint, at least!

00:46:43.512 --> 00:46:44.848
Tell me how I'm supposed to view this whole situation,

00:46:44.872 --> 00:46:46.488
some rules or missions, for example.

00:46:46.512 --> 00:46:49.611
I see. I guess that's what boys in the 21st century like.

00:46:50.151 --> 00:46:51.711
For now, just enjoy the ride.

00:46:51.952 --> 00:46:53.928
A trip is supposed to be fun, you know.

00:46:53.952 --> 00:46:56.381
Viva la vida!

00:46:57.222 --> 00:46:58.968
You'll hear from me again.

00:46:58.992 --> 00:47:00.622
All right, then. Bye.

00:47:02.591 --> 00:47:04.291
Hello?

00:47:04.791 --> 00:47:06.908
Don't hang up!

00:47:06.932 --> 00:47:10.032
Don't hang up, please!

00:47:39.332 --> 00:47:40.731
From the reason I ended up here...

00:47:42.762 --> 00:47:44.171
to how I can get back,

00:47:46.302 --> 00:47:47.982
I have to figure out everything on my own?

00:47:50.312 --> 00:47:51.341
That means...

00:47:53.881 --> 00:47:57.052
I'll be stuck here for a while.

00:48:04.191 --> 00:48:07.162
(Baekwang High School)

00:48:07.562 --> 00:48:09.437
(Ignite your passion to enjoy your youth to the fullest!)

00:48:09.461 --> 00:48:11.941
(Contact us to join the band, First Love Memory Manipulators.)

00:48:17.332 --> 00:48:18.401
Nice.

00:48:21.472 --> 00:48:22.541
It's all over.

00:48:23.912 --> 00:48:26.071
It's over? What do you mean?

00:48:26.271 --> 00:48:28.758
Yoon Dong Jin just posted on the forum,

00:48:28.782 --> 00:48:30.251
calling us con artists.

00:48:30.452 --> 00:48:31.452
What?

00:48:33.651 --> 00:48:36.357
Hey, that wasn't a con. It was just a misunderstanding.

00:48:36.381 --> 00:48:38.198
That's what you think.

00:48:38.222 --> 00:48:40.091
Hey, let's go meet him now.

00:48:40.262 --> 00:48:41.897
We should apologize to him properly in person,

00:48:41.921 --> 00:48:43.138
clear up the misunderstanding,

00:48:43.162 --> 00:48:45.242
- and officially ask him to join...
- It's too late.

00:48:45.791 --> 00:48:47.808
An indie band in Hongdae that recognized him that day...

00:48:47.832 --> 00:48:49.337
approached him and recruited him on the spot.

00:48:49.361 --> 00:48:50.501
It's game over.

00:48:56.472 --> 00:48:59.142
First, post a public apology on the forum.

00:48:59.211 --> 00:49:00.288
Then let's post another ad to...

00:49:00.312 --> 00:49:02.718
He also posted a warning telling people not to be fooled...

00:49:02.742 --> 00:49:04.702
even if they saw our ad looking for a new member.

00:49:04.881 --> 00:49:07.297
My gosh. This guy is a good writer.

00:49:07.321 --> 00:49:08.622
People are going wild over this.

00:49:09.622 --> 00:49:10.622
In the band scene,

00:49:12.622 --> 00:49:14.222
we're already done for.

00:49:22.231 --> 00:49:23.571
Give up already, Yi Chan.

00:49:24.271 --> 00:49:25.707
It's always beautiful to see those...

00:49:25.731 --> 00:49:27.872
who leave because they know it's time to give up.

00:49:28.872 --> 00:49:30.742
- Do you think Se Gyeong knows too?
- What?

00:49:31.171 --> 00:49:32.611
That the band is done for.

00:49:32.812 --> 00:49:34.288
Goodness. I'm sure she knows.

00:49:34.312 --> 00:49:35.488
I hear people are betting money...

00:49:35.512 --> 00:49:37.793
on whether or not we can pull this off, so she must know.

00:49:40.251 --> 00:49:41.282
Where are you going?

00:49:42.352 --> 00:49:44.291
I must tell Se Gyeong the truth.

00:49:44.722 --> 00:49:46.321
She'll understand.

00:49:47.821 --> 00:49:49.238
Will one week be enough?

00:49:49.262 --> 00:49:51.167
To get over the rejection?

00:49:51.191 --> 00:49:53.932
No, to find a new member.

00:49:54.631 --> 00:49:55.631
What?

00:49:56.802 --> 00:49:59.377
I'm going to tell Se Gyeong that we're starting over.

00:49:59.401 --> 00:50:01.941
I'll tell her to just ignore the rumors and wait for me.

00:50:02.642 --> 00:50:06.118
You. Keep printing the ad.

00:50:06.142 --> 00:50:08.082
We got this. I, Ha Yi Chan, can do this!

00:50:08.541 --> 00:50:10.782
Darn you! I really can't stand him!

00:50:11.211 --> 00:50:12.312
Darn it.

00:50:19.392 --> 00:50:20.392
My gosh!

00:50:20.622 --> 00:50:22.262
Well, about yesterday...

00:50:23.392 --> 00:50:24.562
I'm really sorry!

00:50:26.901 --> 00:50:30.472
Wait. Would I be able to join you instead of him?

00:50:32.472 --> 00:50:34.642
- What are you talking about?
- The band.

00:50:34.941 --> 00:50:37.021
The thing is, I can play the guitar pretty well too.

00:50:37.912 --> 00:50:40.272
The new member will be provided with room and board, right?

00:50:40.312 --> 00:50:41.888
Would I be able to stay at the guesthouse...

00:50:41.912 --> 00:50:43.952
instead of Yoon Dong Jin?

00:50:44.812 --> 00:50:47.651
My gosh. Have you no shame?

00:50:48.481 --> 00:50:50.127
I can't stay long anyway.

00:50:50.151 --> 00:50:51.791
Just until I find a way to go back...

00:50:53.291 --> 00:50:55.331
Do you know what I had to deal with because of you?

00:50:55.722 --> 00:50:56.937
I'm sorry, but can you let go of...

00:50:56.961 --> 00:50:59.131
People in the band scene call me a con artist,

00:50:59.432 --> 00:51:01.401
and Se Gyeong thinks I'm a failure.

00:51:01.961 --> 00:51:04.102
If only you hadn't duped me that day...

00:51:04.472 --> 00:51:05.778
or hadn't followed me,

00:51:05.802 --> 00:51:08.118
I wouldn't be in this ridiculous mess now.

00:51:08.142 --> 00:51:09.202
Do you realize that?

00:51:09.602 --> 00:51:11.247
Well, there's nothing I can do about that.

00:51:11.271 --> 00:51:12.312
You little...

00:51:12.441 --> 00:51:13.881
You'd better hide well.

00:51:14.481 --> 00:51:16.341
If I see you again, you're dead meat.

00:51:18.082 --> 00:51:20.111
- Don't be like this, please.
- Don't follow me.

00:51:22.952 --> 00:51:24.151
I said not to follow me!

00:51:26.052 --> 00:51:27.091
The truth is,

00:51:28.421 --> 00:51:29.892
I have nowhere to go.

00:51:34.332 --> 00:51:35.361
Gosh.

00:51:35.731 --> 00:51:37.372
Wait!

00:51:40.771 --> 00:51:43.202
Just a moment. Wait up! Gosh, seriously!

00:51:44.611 --> 00:51:45.671
Se Gyeong!

00:51:49.381 --> 00:51:50.428
Have you heard the rumors?

00:51:50.452 --> 00:51:51.928
Rumors? About what?

00:51:51.952 --> 00:51:54.352
You know, that guy who bet with you the other day.

00:51:54.452 --> 00:51:56.127
That wacko from Baekwang High, Ha Yi Chan.

00:51:56.151 --> 00:51:57.821
Oh, him. What about him?

00:51:58.222 --> 00:52:00.837
He got himself in trouble, trying to start a band.

00:52:00.861 --> 00:52:03.392
This time, his plan failed miserably.

00:52:03.662 --> 00:52:05.538
Good. He failed even sooner than I thought.

00:52:05.562 --> 00:52:06.961
I know, right?

00:52:07.861 --> 00:52:08.861
Wait.

00:52:09.631 --> 00:52:11.731
What's this? A love letter?

00:52:13.841 --> 00:52:16.081
(Myeongse Med School Band Golden Scalpel's 10th Concert)

00:52:16.142 --> 00:52:17.171
What?

00:52:17.372 --> 00:52:20.782
This is a ticket to Ji Hwan's band's concert.

00:52:21.242 --> 00:52:22.642
Is this for me?

00:52:23.142 --> 00:52:24.512
I'm sorry to disappoint you,

00:52:25.812 --> 00:52:26.852
but this isn't for you.

00:52:27.352 --> 00:52:29.052
What? Then where is mine?

00:52:29.651 --> 00:52:31.622
Who is it for?

00:53:01.381 --> 00:53:03.261
(Do you like band music? Do you like that guy?)

00:53:12.461 --> 00:53:14.661
I have to say, this episode was a little disappointing.

00:53:14.861 --> 00:53:16.901
I was hoping there would be a twist. What a bummer.

00:53:34.782 --> 00:53:35.821
(Western Art 1920-1960)

00:54:00.512 --> 00:54:01.992
That idiot is like a wet autumn leaf.

00:54:03.751 --> 00:54:05.431
He's glued to me and won't leave me alone.

00:54:08.981 --> 00:54:10.901
(Seowon Arts High School, Outsiders Not Allowed)

00:54:13.352 --> 00:54:14.392
Shoot.

00:54:14.961 --> 00:54:16.021
Ha Yi Chan?

00:54:17.532 --> 00:54:20.401
Hey, Jun Ki. My gosh.

00:54:21.501 --> 00:54:22.508
Do you go to this school?

00:54:22.532 --> 00:54:24.731
Yes. Hey, what happened?

00:54:24.972 --> 00:54:26.377
Is it true that you can't start a band?

00:54:26.401 --> 00:54:28.501
- I bet my money on you, so I'm...
- Yi Chan!

00:54:28.872 --> 00:54:30.441
Ha Yi Chan!

00:54:32.242 --> 00:54:33.571
Oh, why...

00:54:33.912 --> 00:54:35.082
I love you, Jun Ki.

00:54:35.242 --> 00:54:38.282
No, Yi Chan. We can't do this.

00:54:38.552 --> 00:54:40.421
No. Wait, Yi Chan.

00:54:41.321 --> 00:54:42.821
Thank you for everything you do.

00:54:42.952 --> 00:54:44.521
My pleasure. Have a good day.

00:54:45.921 --> 00:54:46.992
- Stop.
- Wait.

00:54:48.521 --> 00:54:49.961
- Wait here.
- Yi Chan!

00:54:50.021 --> 00:54:51.908
- Ha Yi Chan!
- Hey!

00:54:51.932 --> 00:54:53.267
We need to talk.

00:54:53.291 --> 00:54:54.432
About what?

00:54:56.832 --> 00:54:58.501
(Seowon Arts High School)

00:54:58.702 --> 00:54:59.702
Okay.

00:55:03.001 --> 00:55:04.921
Hey, you. Can you throw the ball back over here?

00:55:08.441 --> 00:55:09.481
The left hand...

00:55:14.352 --> 00:55:15.329
- will only assist...
- What?

00:55:15.353 --> 00:55:16.952
That's Ha Yi Chan from Baekwang High.

00:55:17.751 --> 00:55:18.991
Who? Is he a basketball player?

00:55:19.191 --> 00:55:21.421
The name rings a bell, but...

00:55:22.821 --> 00:55:23.932
I must run.

00:55:24.691 --> 00:55:25.791
That little...

00:55:37.341 --> 00:55:38.412
Hey!

00:55:38.642 --> 00:55:39.671
Stop right there!

00:55:40.271 --> 00:55:41.758
Why is he so fast?

00:55:41.782 --> 00:55:43.582
- Catch me if you can.
- Stop right there!

00:56:44.171 --> 00:56:46.441
This little rat. Where did he go?

00:56:48.682 --> 00:56:49.782
Did he go that way?

00:56:59.952 --> 00:57:00.992
Is he here?

00:57:04.432 --> 00:57:05.432
Darn it.

00:57:19.441 --> 00:57:20.472
Where is he?

00:57:20.742 --> 00:57:22.312
I swear, I heard his voice just now.

00:57:26.952 --> 00:57:28.921
Gosh, why is he taking so long?

00:57:55.711 --> 00:57:57.041
Please stay put.

00:57:58.251 --> 00:58:01.381
I promise to repay you for your help before I die.

00:58:08.421 --> 00:58:09.421
Ma'am.

00:58:12.791 --> 00:58:13.951
Did you just call me "Ma'am?"

00:58:14.302 --> 00:58:15.731
My gosh. It really is you.

00:58:18.832 --> 00:58:21.501
I had no idea I'd run into you here, ma'am.

00:58:36.052 --> 00:58:38.791
(Special thanks to Kim Seul Gi and Kim Jun Hyung)

00:59:05.352 --> 00:59:09.981
(Twinkling Watermelon)

00:59:10.082 --> 00:59:12.727
I thought my life was always meant to shine.

00:59:12.751 --> 00:59:15.238
Was she the reason you wanted to start a band?

00:59:15.262 --> 00:59:17.098
Until I met this fool.

00:59:17.122 --> 00:59:18.107
I was immature...

00:59:18.131 --> 00:59:20.707
for thinking I should start a band because I was so in love.

00:59:20.731 --> 00:59:22.178
I'm leaving next week to go study abroad.

00:59:22.202 --> 00:59:23.361
For now, it's a secret.

00:59:23.432 --> 00:59:26.107
Why? Because of Ha Yi Chan at Baekwang High?

00:59:26.131 --> 00:59:28.417
What happened to Dad...

00:59:28.441 --> 00:59:30.348
when he was 18?

00:59:30.372 --> 00:59:31.888
Do you actually want to start a band?

00:59:31.912 --> 00:59:34.118
You just want to be popular with girls.

00:59:34.142 --> 00:59:36.187
I told you. He goes to Chuncheon National University of Education.

00:59:36.211 --> 00:59:37.852
I'm going to be his tutor.
